29:37.792 --> 29:39.792
PETER: Oh, no, no, no,
you got it backwards.

29:39.875 --> 29:42.041
It was-- it was-- it was she
who made the sale.

29:42.125 --> 29:44.291
JONATHAN: I get that, but you
did your fair share of the work.

29:44.375 --> 29:45.750
PETER: She is a ball buster.

29:45.834 --> 29:48.500
-She can be
really fucking scary.
-MIRA: Oh my God.

29:48.583 --> 29:50.709
PETER: And she's a--
she's a true artist, right?

29:50.792 --> 29:53.500
-I'll call a car.
-PETER: She's a certifiable
genius. She's gorgeous.

29:53.583 --> 29:55.083
I'm just gonna clean up a bit.

29:55.166 --> 29:57.458
PETER: I don't know why she even
ever let me between her legs,

29:57.542 --> 29:59.291
this paragon of perfection.

29:59.375 --> 30:00.333
KATE: Hi. I need a car

30:00.417 --> 30:04.125
at 206 Abbottsford Road
in Brookline.

30:04.208 --> 30:07.000
PETER: When I sleep with
other women, it's because, uh,

30:07.083 --> 30:09.458
it's only because
it makes me feel...

30:10.458 --> 30:12.166
You know, it's--
it has nothing to do

30:12.250 --> 30:15.333
with falling in love.
It's the only way--

30:15.417 --> 30:18.041
It's the only way
that I can, uh...

30:18.125 --> 30:19.291
JONATHAN: No, it does--

30:19.375 --> 30:20.875
PETER: You know, I know--
I know I'm the one who--

30:20.959 --> 30:23.208
Peter, I called us a car.
Neither one of us can drive.

30:23.291 --> 30:27.166
-PETER: Mm-hmm. Yeah.
-JONATHAN: Do you want coffee
or anything?

30:27.250 --> 30:29.208
-KATE: Are you okay?
-Yeah, I'm good. Yeah.

30:29.291 --> 30:31.000
Yeah, I was just, uh...

30:31.083 --> 30:32.709
I was just trying
to explain to him

30:32.792 --> 30:36.083
how you and I decided to, uh...

30:36.166 --> 30:39.583
And I, you know, I was saying
that just ignoring the fact

30:39.667 --> 30:42.333
that you have options
doesn't make them go away.

30:42.417 --> 30:43.500
-Right? Right?
-KATE: Yeah.

30:43.583 --> 30:45.583
PETER: You know, or another way
of saying it is,

30:45.667 --> 30:48.208
you know, if the only reason
that you're faithful

30:48.291 --> 30:51.041
is because it's like
a rational decision,

30:51.125 --> 30:53.250
-well, that's not sustainable.
-Why not?

30:53.333 --> 30:55.458
Well, because it's just a matter
of the right woman, right time

30:55.542 --> 30:57.458
-when it finally happens, right?
-JONATHAN: Oh, okay.

30:57.542 --> 30:59.375
So I don't have a choice
in the matter?

30:59.458 --> 31:00.709
PETER: No, you don't.

31:00.792 --> 31:02.792
Because, I mean, this force...

31:02.875 --> 31:06.208
-(WHISPERING) I'm tired.
-...call it Eros or whatever,

31:06.291 --> 31:08.667
you know, it's far more powerful
than your own will.

31:08.750 --> 31:10.083
The car is on the way.

31:10.166 --> 31:11.375
You better start
getting ready, okay?

31:11.458 --> 31:13.083
PETER: Just a second.
You understand what I'm saying?

31:13.166 --> 31:14.417
JONATHAN:
It depends on who you are.

31:14.500 --> 31:16.125
-No, it doesn't! It doesn't!
-Shh. Peter.

31:16.208 --> 31:17.458
-Quiet.
-PETER: I'm sorry.

31:17.542 --> 31:19.250
JONATHAN: I think it's just--
it's a longer conversation.

31:19.333 --> 31:20.834
No, tell me, I wanna hear.

31:23.500 --> 31:25.917
I think maybe it's just because
of the way that I was raised.

31:26.000 --> 31:28.583
-PETER: What do you mean?
-Well, you know, in...

31:28.667 --> 31:30.917
the first 20 years of your life,

31:31.000 --> 31:34.083
you're taught to conquer
your desires,

31:34.166 --> 31:36.208
-not surrender to them.
-Dude.

31:36.291 --> 31:38.625
-JONATHAN: What?
-That's grotesque.

31:38.709 --> 31:39.750
JONATHAN: Maybe.

31:39.834 --> 31:41.500
I mean,
that level of repression,

31:41.583 --> 31:42.667
it's like from the Middle Ages.

31:42.750 --> 31:43.750
JONATHAN: I'm not defending it.

31:43.834 --> 31:45.250
I'm just saying
that it's ingrained in me.

31:45.333 --> 31:46.500
Hey, babe, where is your jacket?

31:46.583 --> 31:48.083
-PETER: Just a second.
-We need to get ready.

31:48.166 --> 31:50.583
You really need
to start shaking that off.

31:50.667 --> 31:52.750
-Or it's gonna take
a major toll on you.
-KATE: Peter.

31:52.834 --> 31:54.041
PETER: Not just mentally,
I mean,

31:54.125 --> 31:56.208
physically
and spiritually, and...

31:56.291 --> 31:58.125
-The car is almost here.
-Yeah, I heard you!

31:58.208 --> 32:00.041
-He can wait a minute!
-Shh.

32:00.875 --> 32:02.250
(AVA CRYING)

32:04.333 --> 32:05.834
Shit.

32:05.917 --> 32:07.500
-MIRA: Here.
-PETER: I'm sorry.

32:07.583 --> 32:09.375
-KATE: I'm really sorry.
-I call you tomorrow.

32:10.792 --> 32:12.500
-Mira, I'm sorry.
-Yeah.

32:13.667 --> 32:15.375
I'm sorry.
I apologize.

32:15.458 --> 32:17.667
-Bye. Night.
-JONATHAN: No worries.
It's all right.

32:17.750 --> 32:19.291
-PETER: Is she mad at me?
-KATE: Peter, let's go.

32:19.375 --> 32:21.250
JONATHAN: It's fine. It's fine.
It's just a long day.

32:21.333 --> 32:22.875
All right, guys.
Thanks for coming.

32:22.959 --> 32:24.417
-KATE: Okay.
-JONATHAN: Don't worry about it.

32:24.500 --> 32:26.000
KATE: So we'll come back
for our car tomorrow?

32:26.083 --> 32:28.542
-JONATHAN: Uh, is it that one?
-KATE: No, it's across
the street.

32:28.625 --> 32:30.166
(INDISTINCT CHATTER CONTINUES)

32:30.250 --> 32:31.917
(AVA SIGHS)

32:35.208 --> 32:36.667
JONATHAN: You're welcome. Bye.

32:36.750 --> 32:37.959
