and confident about this--

41:22.333 --> 41:24.834
Yeah, but-- that's because I see
how ambivalent you are about it.

41:24.917 --> 41:27.333
-Well, yeah.
Of course I'm ambivalent.
-JONATHAN: Yeah.

41:27.417 --> 41:29.333
I mean, you remember
those first two years with Ava?

41:29.417 --> 41:30.959
-Yeah.
-Thinking about jumping back

41:31.041 --> 41:32.125
into that nightmare.

41:32.208 --> 41:33.834
Yeah. I was there too.
I remember.

41:33.917 --> 41:36.625
MIRA: I know you were. I know
you've been an amazing partner,

41:36.709 --> 41:38.166
but you don't--
you couldn't, like--

41:38.250 --> 41:39.375
JONATHAN:
I couldn't-- I couldn't be

41:39.458 --> 41:40.583
-where you were.
-No, you could not.

41:40.667 --> 41:42.291
JONATHAN: I couldn't be
in your place. I know.

41:42.375 --> 41:43.458
You tried and...

41:44.458 --> 41:45.625
But you couldn't.

41:47.750 --> 41:50.000
I took that out on you.
I took it--

41:50.083 --> 41:52.709
I was just awful to you.
I was awful.

41:52.792 --> 41:54.792
We-- we talked about it,

41:54.875 --> 41:56.542
and I understood
where that came from.

41:56.625 --> 41:57.917
-You know?
-I know you understood,

41:58.000 --> 42:00.083
but you were also hurt.

42:01.125 --> 42:03.458
That's why you become distant,
and I hated you

42:03.542 --> 42:06.125
for being distant, and I hated
myself even more for...

42:06.792 --> 42:08.500
being so shitty to you.

42:10.709 --> 42:13.458
-I felt like a terrible mom.
-Oh, sweetie, I...

42:14.792 --> 42:16.625
That was a nightmare for you.

42:16.709 --> 42:18.375
It was a nightmare
for both of us.

42:18.458 --> 42:19.500
Yeah.

42:21.000 --> 42:23.834
And it took so long to, like...

42:23.917 --> 42:26.000
feel like myself again,
you know?

42:26.083 --> 42:27.834
And now we're good, and...

42:28.750 --> 42:30.542
And Ava's so good, and...

42:30.625 --> 42:32.417
Especially
when she's with you, she's--

42:32.500 --> 42:35.041
-Aw, come on.
-Kidding.

42:35.834 --> 42:36.834
(CLEARS THROAT)

42:38.875 --> 42:40.625
It's just like I finally...

42:42.166 --> 42:45.291
returned to my life.

42:49.000 --> 42:50.834
I feel so guilty
about what I'm saying.

42:50.917 --> 42:52.583
Sweetie, you shouldn't
feel guilty.

42:52.667 --> 42:54.333
It makes perfect sense,
you know?

42:54.417 --> 42:56.000
Yeah. (SNIFFLES)

42:58.667 --> 43:01.083
It's like, um...

43:01.166 --> 43:04.375
all of a sudden,
everything is unreal.

43:06.166 --> 43:07.834
Everything that we had,

43:08.917 --> 43:10.250
you, you're not real.

43:10.333 --> 43:12.959
Ava isn't. It's just--
it's this thing.

43:13.041 --> 43:16.417
It's this pregnancy.
It's the only thing that's real.

43:16.500 --> 43:19.208
-It's...
-Hey, Mira.

43:20.208 --> 43:21.166
Yeah.

43:21.250 --> 43:23.000
-Babe.
-What?

43:27.709 --> 43:29.959
Mm. (SNIFFLES)

43:30.041 --> 43:32.291
It's painful wanting something
and not wanting it

43:32.375 --> 43:34.291
at the same time.
You know?

43:34.375 --> 43:36.875
JONATHAN: Yeah, yeah.

43:38.667 --> 43:40.333
But think about it.

43:41.959 --> 43:45.000
-Yeah.
-When Ava was a baby,
we had no perspective at all.

43:45.083 --> 43:46.834
We thought it was
gonna be like that forever.

43:46.917 --> 43:49.125
-Right.
-And now we see
that it passes, right?

43:50.083 --> 43:53.000
-(MIRA SNIFFLES)
-It gets better. Right?

43:53.083 --> 43:54.917
-That's true.
-Yeah.

43:58.792 --> 44:01.667
You know, Ava's totally obsessed
with having a little sister.

44:01.750 --> 44:03.375
-Yeah.
-If it's....

44:03.458 --> 44:04.750
a boy, that'll be rough.

44:04.834 --> 44:07.208
Well, it'll have to
be a girl then.

44:07.291 --> 44:09.291
We'll raise it a girl,
regardless.

44:16.875 --> 44:19.041
Either way, they're gonna want
their own rooms eventually.

44:19.125 --> 44:20.208
Mm-hmm.

44:20.291 --> 44:21.959
But it should be a pretty easy
renovation, you know,

44:22.041 --> 44:24.792
to divide Ava's room in half.

44:26.333 --> 44:29.208
We'll have to steal a little
square footage from the hallway,

44:29.291 --> 44:31.000
put up a little drywall, right?

44:31.083 --> 44:32.125
Sure.

44:37.000 --> 44:39.041
I love you.
You know that, right?

44:39.125 --> 44:40.291
Yes, I do.

44:41.542 --> 44:42.917
(SIGHS)

44:44.834 --> 44:48.542
♪ (SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

44:48.625 --> 44:51.792
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

44:52.959 --> 44:56.792
(SPRINKLER RUNNING)

45:10.166 --> 45:12.166
(CLOCK TICKING)

45:26.667 --> 45:28.417
(KNOCKING)

45:28.500 --> 45:31.458
-DR. VARONA: Yup, come in.
-Hi? Sorry. Am I late? I'm late.

45:31.542 --> 45:34.208
MIRA: It's fine. We just, uh--
we're just starting out.

45:34.291 --> 45:36.000
-Sorry. Sorry.
-DR. VARONA: Yeah, no problem.

45:36.083 --> 45:38.583
-Nice... nice to see you.
-Good to see you.

45:38.667 --> 45:40.417
DR. VARONA: So, I was just
starting to explain

45:40.500 --> 45:42.375
-the procedure to Mira.
-Great.

45:44.166 --> 45:47.375
DR. VARONA:
As I said, you'll take
the mifepristone here today,

45:47.458 --> 45:48.834
and that blocks
your progesterone,

45:48.917 --> 45:50.583
effectively ending
the pregnancy.

45:50.667 --> 45:53.417
And then I'll send you home
with four pills of misoprostol,

45:53.500 --> 45:55.208
and that'll bring on
contractions.

45:55.291 --> 45:58.667
-MIRA: Mm-hmm.
-So that can be not so fun.

45:58.750 --> 46:01.291
You'll have cramping
and heavy bleeding.

46:01.375 --> 46:03.417
You'll pass some large clots,

46:03.500 --> 46:05.417
and you might have nausea,

46:05.500 --> 46:09.417
vomiting, diarrhea, dizziness,
and in rare cases, fever.

46:10.125 --> 46:12.709
It's like a stomach virus.

46:14.375 --> 46:15.792
Great.

46:15.875 --> 46:17.208
DR. VARONA:
So that's all normal.

46:17.291 --> 46:20.208
But if you have any side effects
that worry you, just call.

46:21.750 --> 46:24.000
Does it still seem
like what you wanna do?

46:26.500 --> 46:27.959
Yeah.

46:28.041 --> 46:29.291
DR. VARONA: While you're here,

46:29.375 --> 46:31.333
do you wanna talk
about contraception,

46:31.417 --> 46:33.625
since the pill
wasn't your friend this time?

46:33.709 --> 46:35.458
Yeah, I was just
saying to Jonathan

46:35.542 --> 46:37.333
that I was amazed that, um,

46:37.417 --> 46:39.458
could still have an accident
at my age.

46:40.083 --> 46:41.834
You'll be...

46:41.917 --> 46:44.000
-40 in November, right?
-Mm-hmm.

46:44.083 --> 46:45.417
DR. VARONA: Yeah.
That's gonna keep

46:45.500 --> 46:47.250
-getting less likely.
-MIRA: Yeah, totally.

46:47.333 --> 46:48.583
DR. VARONA:
But in the meantime--

46:48.667 --> 46:50.333
So there are a bunch
of long-term options.

46:50.417 --> 46:52.291
There's Implanon,
which is an arm insert.

46:52.375 --> 46:53.959
-I could place that here today.
-Mm-hmm.

46:54.041 --> 46:56.125
DR. VARONA: And there are IUDs,
the ParaGard,

46:56.208 --> 46:57.875
which is plain copper,

46:57.959 --> 46:59.083
or the Mirena,

46:59.166 --> 47:01.375
which is very popular,
it's a hormone-releasing IUD.

47:02.250 --> 47:03.500
MIRA: Maybe the copper one.

47:03.583 --> 47:05.166
It would be nice to give
my body a break

47:05.250 --> 47:06.750
-from all those hormones.
-DR. VARONA: Mm-hmm.

47:06.834 --> 47:08.834
Yeah. Well, I can place that
at your follow-up.

47:08.917 --> 47:11.375
-And, uh, you can think about it
a little more.
-Okay.

47:11.458 --> 47:14.291
DR. VARONA:
For now, just throw out
your current package of pills

47:14.375 --> 47:16.166
and start a new one tomorrow.

47:16.250 --> 47:17.625
-Okay?
-Yeah.

47:18.583 --> 47:20.291
DR. VARONA: Any questions?

47:21.417 --> 47:22.417
MIRA: Nope.

47:22.500 --> 47:24.625
DR. VARONA: Okay.
I'm gonna go get the medicine.

47:24.709 --> 47:25.750
Okay.

47:28.792 --> 47:29.834
(DOOR CLOSES)

47:31.000 --> 47:32.834
MIRA: She has to warn us
about the symptoms,

47:32.917 --> 47:35.166
but it's, uh,
it's the simplest procedure.

47:35.250 --> 47:37.083
Yeah. Yeah. No, I know. I know.

47:40.583 --> 47:42.583
I'm gonna get us
something to drink.

47:42.667 --> 47:43.625
Diet Coke, is that good?

47:43.709 --> 47:45.208
No, I don't need--
I don't need anything.

47:45.291 --> 47:46.917
No, I'll get us one.
There's a vending machine

47:47.000 --> 47:48.208
right outside the door.

47:48.291 --> 47:51.125
Um, yeah.
I'll be right back, okay?

47:51.625 --> 47:53.000
MIRA: Uh, fine.

48:00.250 --> 48:04.333
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

48:19.208 --> 48:20.500
(CAN DROPS)

48:29.792 --> 48:31.792
Hey? I'll be right there.

48:31.875 --> 48:32.875
Okay.

48:36.041 --> 48:39.417
(BREATHES IN, CLEARS THROAT)

48:45.500 --> 48:48.417
Hey. So, they only had Pepsi.

48:48.500 --> 48:49.500
-Is that okay?
-That's fine.

48:49.583 --> 48:50.834
-JONATHAN: It's all right?
-Mm-hmm.

48:50.917 --> 48:52.250
JONATHAN: I'm sure
there's, like, a cup

48:52.333 --> 48:53.875
around here somewhere.

48:53.959 --> 48:56.291
MIRA: No, it's fine. I'll just
drink it straight from the can.

48:56.375 --> 48:58.166
I'm sure there's something.
Maybe here.

48:58.250 --> 48:59.250
MIRA: Jonathan.

48:59.333 --> 49:00.792
Oh, I think
there's something here.

49:00.875 --> 49:02.125
MIRA: Come here for a second.

49:02.208 --> 49:03.750
Oh, fuck,
it's a urine sample cup.

49:03.834 --> 49:06.208
Okay. Come over here.
Sit down for a second.

49:11.750 --> 49:13.166
(JONATHAN SIGHS)

49:13.250 --> 49:14.417
Look at me.

49:16.583 --> 49:18.458
(LAUGHS)

49:20.291 --> 49:21.417
Are you okay?

49:21.500 --> 49:23.959
-Yeah.
-Are you mad?

49:24.041 --> 49:26.542
Am I mad? No.
Why would I be mad?

49:27.458 --> 49:28.917
MIRA: Are you having
second thoughts?

49:30.166 --> 49:31.125
No.

49:31.208 --> 49:32.959
-MIRA: No?
-No, no, no, no. I...

49:37.750 --> 49:39.250
-I don't--
-I'm just--

49:39.333 --> 49:41.000
I don't why
I'm feeling like this.

49:41.083 --> 49:42.750
I didn't expect
to feel like that.

49:43.417 --> 49:44.834
No, it's okay, honey.

49:44.917 --> 49:47.083
-It's fine.
-JONATHAN: Yeah.

49:47.166 --> 49:49.667
You know, I'm-- it's not easy
for me either.

49:49.750 --> 49:52.166
JONATHAN: No, no, no, no, no.
Of course. Of course. Uh...

49:52.250 --> 49:54.917
Sorry, I'm not, um, trying
to make-- No, yeah.

49:55.000 --> 49:59.166
I know you-- you're the one that
has to-- has to go through it.

50:03.333 --> 50:06.458
We're making
the right decision here.

50:07.792 --> 50:09.792
We talked about it.

50:09.875 --> 50:12.709
I don't think there's a single
angle that we haven't covered

50:12.792 --> 50:14.959
over the last ten days.

50:15.041 --> 50:16.959
Yeah, I don't--
I don't think there is.

50:18.041 --> 50:19.125
JONATHAN: Yeah.

50:29.458 --> 50:30.667
You know, I was thinking

50:30.750 --> 50:33.333
we could still go ahead
with the renovation.

50:33.417 --> 50:34.792
-You know? Like--
-No.

50:34.875 --> 50:38.625
MIRA: Yeah. Like, we can move
Ava's play area into her room

50:38.709 --> 50:41.583
and, you know, make your study
back the way that it was before.

50:41.667 --> 50:42.583
That's never gonna work.

50:42.667 --> 50:43.917
She's gonna reclaim it
within hours.

50:44.000 --> 50:45.917
Well, then we use the attic.
I mean, we always said that

50:46.000 --> 50:47.458
we were gonna get to that
eventually.

50:47.542 --> 50:49.208
JONATHAN: I'm okay.
I'm good where my office is.

50:49.291 --> 50:50.583
-I don't need--
-Well, I have a vision.

50:50.667 --> 50:52.750
-Just, you know, leave it to me.
-JONATHAN: Okay, okay. Okay.

50:52.834 --> 50:55.333
-You're gonna thank me.
-Okay. Okay.

50:56.417 --> 50:58.041
-(KNOCKING ON DOOR)
-MIRA: Oh.

50:58.125 --> 51:00.166
-DR. VARONA: Sorry about that.
-It's okay.

51:01.041 --> 51:04.000
-Here you go.
-MIRA: Thanks.

51:06.667 --> 51:09.041
(TABLET STUB RATTLING)

51:27.709 --> 51:31.375
DR. VARONA: Okay.
And here's the misoprostol

51:32.375 --> 51:34.208
that you will take at home
tomorrow.

51:34.291 --> 51:35.500
MIRA: Mm-hmm.

51:35.583 --> 51:37.625
DR. VARONA: Take some ibuprofen
about an hour before you put

51:37.709 --> 51:39.709
the tablets in your cheek, okay?

51:41.375 --> 51:42.458
All right. Here you go.

51:42.542 --> 51:44.291
-MIRA: Mm-hmm.
-See you in a couple weeks.

51:44.375 --> 51:45.834
-MIRA: Okay.
-JONATHAN: Thank you.

51:47.458 --> 51:48.458
MIRA: Oh.

51:48.542 --> 51:50.250
-Are you okay?
-Yeah.

51:52.709 --> 51:54.041
(MIRA GROANS)

51:54.125 --> 51:55.959
I feel a little nauseous.

51:56.041 --> 51:57.583
I'm fine. It's fine.

51:57.667 --> 52:00.834
I'm sure, um, it's just
the power of suggestion.

52:00.917 --> 52:04.000
DR. VARONA: Just rest
until it passes, okay?

52:04.083 --> 52:07.375
If you do vomit, you'll have to
take the medicine again.

52:08.417 --> 52:11.625
I'll ask the nurse to check in
on you in a bit.

52:11.709 --> 52:14.291
-Okay. Feel better.
-MIRA: Hmm.

52:17.917 --> 52:20.208
-(DOOR CLOSES)
-(MIRA GROANS QUIETLY)

52:20.750 --> 52:22.417
-You okay?
-Mm-mm.

52:23.917 --> 52:24.917
Okay.

52:35.542 --> 52:37.083
(WHISPERING) I feel awful.

52:40.625 --> 52:42.542
I'm sure you'll feel better
tomorrow.

52:48.375 --> 52:49.875
Why don't you go home to Ava?

52:49.959 --> 52:52.375
-I'll take a car home.
-JONATHAN: No, no. No way.

52:52.458 --> 52:53.792
I'm staying here.

52:53.875 --> 52:56.291
-Veronica's with Ava. She's--
-Jonathan, I--

52:56.792 --> 52:58.709
JONATHAN: What?

52:58.792 --> 53:02.250
I'd like to be alone
for a little bit. Is that okay?

53:03.625 --> 53:04.834
-Yeah.
-MIRA: Yeah?

53:04.917 --> 53:07.041
Of course. Of course.

53:07.125 --> 53:09.166
Here, I'll leave this
right here, okay?

53:09.250 --> 53:10.333
MIRA: Yup. You're not--

53:10.417 --> 53:11.875
-You're sure it's fine?
-Yes, of course, sweetie.

53:11.959 --> 53:14.583
It's fine. It's fine.
I'm totally fine, yeah.

53:14.667 --> 53:17.250
-I'll go do a little work
in the waiting...
-Mm-hmm.

53:17.333 --> 53:19.000
...room over there, okay?
And you just come out

53:19.083 --> 53:20.417
-whenever you're ready.
-MIRA: Yeah, just--

53:20.500 --> 53:22.125
-it won't be long.
-Yeah. Take your time.

53:22.208 --> 53:23.959
-I've got my phone, so...
-Okay.

53:31.333 --> 53:32.625
(DOOR CLOSES)

53:48.250 --> 53:51.959
(SOBBING)

53:58.917 --> 54:01.667
(SOBBING)

54:06.667 --> 54:11.208
♪ (SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

54:24.792 --> 54:27.875
(INSECTS BUZZING)

54:38.125 --> 54:41.417
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

54:47.041 --> 54:50.583
